extendedInfo.description: The official app for Dance Marathon at the University of Florida. Use this app to prepare for the event and stay updated on everything the day of!Dance Marathon at the University of Florida is an annual 26.2-hour event benefiting the patients of Shands Hospital for Children in Gainesville, FL. Each year, more than 800 students stay awake and on their feet to raise money and awareness for Children's Miracle Network Hospitals. In the 18 years of Dance Marathon at UF's existence, more than $5.3 million has been donated, making it the most successful student-run philanthropy in the Southeastern United States. In 2012, DM at UF raised more than $886,000 for Children's Miracle Network Hospitals at Shands Children's Hospital at the University of Florida. Dance Marathon is celebrating it's 19th birthday this spring from April 13 to April 14. Go Gators and FTK!
